  "text_preview": "\"take away\" American Sign Language (ASL) ASL University ► American Sign Language: \"take away\" or \"subtract\" The sign for \"take away\" or \"subtract\" can also mean \"deduct from.\" It can also mean deduct as in a tax deduction. SUBTRACT / MINUS / TAKE-WAY / DEDUCT-from: Sentence: 18 take away 5 equals what? When teaching math, sometimes you might want to use the NEGATIVE sign since it can be interpreted as meaning \"minus. MINUS or NEGATIVE: Also see: TAKE Also see: BRING Want to help support ASL University? It's easy : DONATE ( Thanks! ) (You don't need a PayPal account. Just look for the credit card logos and click continue). For a list of various ways to donate see: https://www.Lifeprint.com/donate Another way to help is to buy something from the ASLU \" Bookstore .\" A must see!: ASL Universit"
}
